  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT365-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">“yāṉ varaiyun tuṇaiyum āṟṟavallaḷō” eṉa viṉāya kiḻavaṟkut tōḻi colliyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by the confidante to HIM, who asked “won't she
          have the strength, until I marry [her]?” </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT365">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> kōṭī rilaṅkuvaḷai nekiḻa nāḷum</l>
          <l> pāṭila kaliḻntu paṉiyā ṉāvē</l>
          <l> tuṉṉaru neṭuvarait tatumpiya varuvi</l>
          <l> taṇṇeṉ muraci ṉimiḻicai kāṭṭu</l>
          <l> maruṅkiṟ koṇṭa palaviṟ</l>
          <l> peruṅka ṉāṭanī nayantōḷ kaṇṇē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>The eyes of the one you longed for, o man from a land of big stones</l>
          <l rend="indent">with jackfruit trees which cling to the sides ,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">where the waterfall, resounding from the long mountain</l>
          <l rend="indent8">difficult to approach,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">displays the rumbling sound of the drum promising coolness </l>
          <l>– they are unending in dew, having cried without sleeping</l>
          <l rend="indent">day per day, so that [her] conch-cut shining bangles become loose.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
